    "DATED MATERIAL, SUBJECT TO CHANGE. PLEASE CONSULT CURRENT UCSD GENERAL CATALOG FOR ANY ADDITIONAL INFORMATION. Effective Fall 2018, major preparation will be required for this major. For details, visit: http://admissions.ucsd.edu/MajorPrep This major offers an excellent preparation for students with a substantial interest in teaching Mathematics in secondary schools. Students interested in ultimately earning a California teaching credential are advised to take this program. Note: CSE 11 or CSE 8A + 8B or ECE 15 are not required but strongly recommended. For more information please visit https://math.ucsd.edu/students/undergraduate/ma32-math-secondary-education-b-a/ NOTE: Students who have taken a vector calculus course at a non-UC college must successfully petition the course for 20E equivalency. Petitions must generally include course syllabus, textbook information and final exam. More information on the petition process for 20E can be found at the following site: https://www.math.ucsd.edu/students/undergraduate/math-20e-equivalency"
